pos_mean_info_list.mean: 抱怨地；发牢骚地；诉苦地
[法] 原告；发牢骚的人；抱怨者

word_mean_info__list.difference: 指因对处境、待遇不满或其他个人因素而愤愤不平地向他人诉苦或自言自语。
侧重因对处境不满、待遇不公或自己有痛苦等而向别人诉说、埋怨。
多指因不满某人或某事而背着人自言自语地发怨言。

bilingual.source: Anyone who does not know how to make the most of his luck has no right to complain if it passes by him.
bilingual.target: 不知道如何充分利用运气的人无权抱怨运气从他身边溜走。

bilingual.source: She likes to complain about the weather.

bilingual.target: 他经常抱怨他的工作量。

bilingual.source: They complain that the service is too slow.
I don't want to hear you complain anymore.
The kids complain that dinner is not tasty.
bilingual.target: 孩子们抱怨晚饭不好吃。

bilingual.source: Customers complain when the service is slow.
bilingual.target: 当服务慢时，顾客会抱怨。

list.abstract: complain（英[kəmˈpleɪn]，美[kəmˈpleɪn]），英语单词。做动词用，指抱怨、发牢骚、诉苦。英语短语有complain about（怨天尤人），例句为People can use them to celebrate or complain.（人们可以用它们来庆祝或抱怨。） 第三人称单数为complains，现在分词为complaining，过去式为complained，过去分词为complained。 近义词有beef about（动词）、rail against（动词）；反义词为cheer。
《Complain》是由春风作词、作曲，春风/伍绍维编曲，悶餅MOONBAND演唱的歌曲，于2021年12月21日发行。

yingyinNormal.en: I've heard you complain about his snoring.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也听你抱怨过他打呼很大声啊。

yingyinNormal.en: Now he's gonna be the guy she goes too to complain about you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在她就会跑去跟他抱怨你。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, Sis, don't mean to complain, but this one's empty. What happened, did you run out of ideas?
yingyinNormal.zh: 妹妹，不是我抱怨，这间房是空的。怎么，点子用光了？

yingyinNormal.en: So, after drinks with Bernadette, I get home, and Penny calls to complain about her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 和伯纳黛特喝了几杯后，我刚到家，佩妮就打来电话抱怨伯纳黛特。

yingyinNormal.en: I'd like to thank you guys for coming down here to complain about the rain and ruin my career.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想要谢谢你们过来这里抱怨这些雨，然后毁了我的事业前途。

yingyinNormal.en: No, of course not, because we don't want to hear you complain about how much you hate the sound of crunching eggshells.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，当然不是，因为我们可不想听到你抱怨我们把冰踩碎的声音有多讨厌。

yingyinNormal.en: Lenard? Yeah, hi, hi. How's it going? Can't complain. Thanks for asking.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莱纳德？好啊。你好吗？没什么不好，不过还是谢谢。

word_usage.usage:
表示“抱怨”
complain指因对待遇、处境不满或自己有痛苦等而向别人诉说，常后接介词about/of。
grumble指因对处境、待遇不满或其他个人因素而怨恨地自言自语或向他人诉苦，常后接介词 about/at，可与 moan 换用。
moan是不正式用法，多指以别人厌烦的方式抱怨、埋怨，常后接介词on/about。

examination_example.sentence: As universities go digital, students are <highlight>complaining</highlight> of a new hit to their finances that's replacing — and sometimes joining — expensive textbooks: pricey online access codes that are required to complete coursework and submit assignments.

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: n. 怨言；牢骚；抗议；控告；控诉；疾病；抱怨；诉苦；发牢骚；控诉状

word_family.mean: v. 抱怨；发牢骚；诉苦；呻吟；主诉；悲叹；悲鸣；咯吱作响

sense_info_list.zh: 抱怨; 不满; 控诉; 诉苦

examination_example.sentence: Kids have been coming to my camp for many years now, and I hardly hear any kids or parents <highlight>complain</highlight> (抱怨) .
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子们来我的营地已经很多年了，我几乎没有听到任何孩子或家长抱怨。

examination_example.sentence: Some teachers <highlight>complain</highlight> that a few students feel sleepy or even fall asleep in class.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些老师抱怨说，一些学生感到困倦，甚至在课堂上睡着了。

examination_example.sentence: People can use them to celebrate or <highlight>complain</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们可以用它们来庆祝或抱怨。
